The paper deals with facial expression analysis using deep learning-based approaches, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of 3D models for facial expression synthesis, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation for deep learning-based AU intensity estimation, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of facial expressions, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
